<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-500-318  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 500 318.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DEC User  July 1989 p27(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Portability brings a 4GL into the Vax environment. (Focusfourth-generation language)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bloor, Robin.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Focus fourth-generation language originated on IBM platformsbut has migrated to the DEC VAX as well as other systems.andP;  Focusis distinguished by its end-user orientation, with powerfulreport-generation and data extract capabilities.andP;  Its 'layered'interface lets end users produce simple reports while providingenough power for programmers to develop more elaborate ones.andO;System managers can limit users to avoid consuming excessivecomputer power.andP;  The language has a graphics module for charts andhistograms, an export facility for microcomputer programs, and acomplete set of business statistical functions.andP;  Level 5, a newexpert-system software kit, complements Focus in InformationBuilders' product line.andP;  The major weaknesses of Focus are itslack of a relational database and its weak dictionary.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Focus (Data base management system) (usage)DEC VAX (Minicomputer) (usage).andO;Topic:     Fourth-Generation LanguagesProgram Development ToolsReport GeneratorsSoftware Migration.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Focus provides an array of end-user tools across many platforms.andO;(chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>